  "description": "A stylish and quite roomy two-chamber refrigerator with a reliable inverter compressor, separate cooling circuits for the working chambers and full support for No Frost technology. The model was introduced to the market by the popular brand LG in 2023 and is positioned by the manufacturer in the upper segment of the mid-price range. The total useful capacity of the device is 387 liters. This model uses an auxiliary cooling channel DoorCooling +, which is located above the doorway. Additional door blowing stabilizes the internal temperature of the storage. The two-chamber refrigerator LG GB-B72BM9DQ is equipped with a FRESHBalancer freshness zone - a special container that can be configured to store either vegetables or fruits. Additionally, there is a FRESHConverter drawer, which makes it possible to store meat and fish without direct freezing. A separate shelf with a folding design is available. There is a bottle holder. The refrigerator door is equipped with hanging trays. The refrigeration and freezing chambers are serviced by the No Frost system, due to which the working space does not require periodic defrosting. The noise generated during operation does not exceed 35 dB.",
